verbose_text: Most patients are from a common Roma (ethnic) origin and homozygous for a single founder splice acceptor variant.2 Here we report the novel Japanese cases of TMEM70 gene variants caused by compound heterozygous variants in a Japanese patient (c.141delG, p.Pro48Argfs * 2, and c.316 +1 G> A; reference sequence GenBank NM_017866.5).
